Title: Target Overview
Describe: agents/s20_comprehensive.py is a teaching-oriented comprehensive agent harness that recombines earlier mechanisms into one runnable loop.
------------------------------------------------------------
[Example]
S01_TARGET_OVERVIEW: Target positioning

[Description]
`agents/s20_comprehensive.py` describes itself as a "Comprehensive Agent" that brings dispatch, permissions, hooks, todos, subagents, skills, compaction, memory, error recovery, task graphs, background tasks, cron, teams, protocols, autonomous agents, worktrees, and MCP back into one loop.

Source evidence appears in `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:2-12`.

The runtime entry point is the `__main__` block at `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:2034-2068`, which initializes `history` and `context`, starts `cron_autorun_loop`, and enters the interactive CLI.

Model calls require `MODEL_ID`; the Anthropic client is created at import time after `load_dotenv(override=True)`.

The source baseline is git commit `8462599`; this English report was generated on 2026-06-03.

[UML]
None

[Detail]
This report covers a single Python file and treats the analyzed source as read-only.

It does not analyze the surrounding frontend visualization code.

The file is valuable as a teaching integration harness rather than as a production decomposition: readers can follow how tool schemas, local handlers, task state, teammate messages, plan approval, context budgeting, and retries cooperate inside one model loop.

------------------------------------------------------------
[Example]
Runtime boundaries and reader expectations

[Description]
This file directly touches the filesystem, git, threads, stdin, the Anthropic Messages API, and local mock MCP servers.

Important local state paths include `.tasks`, `.worktrees`, `.mailboxes`, `.transcripts`, `.task_outputs/tool-results`, `.memory/MEMORY.md`, and `.scheduled_tasks.json`.

These paths are declared or created through module-level constants and import-time setup at `agents/s20_comprehensive.py:33-54`, `74-75`, `174-175`, `475-476`, `1279`, and `1840-1841`.

[UML]
None

[Detail]
Read the file as a single-file integration lab.

The same state can be accessed by the CLI path, background tool workers, cron threads, and teammate threads.

Later sections call out which state is guarded by locks, which state relies on simplified file operations, and which tool actions pass through the permission hook.

